cnt2Interface.name: cnt2Interface
cnt2Interface.contactinfo: Computer Network Technology Technical Support 6000 Nathan Lane North Plymouth, Minnesota 55442 telephone: (763) 268-6000 fax: (763) 268-6800 support: 1-800-NET-TECH
cnt2Interface.description: This defines the CNT Interface MIB.

cnt2IfNumTable.name: cnt2IfNumTable
cnt2IfNumTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of cnt2IfNumber.

cnt2IfNumEntry.name: cnt2IfNumEntry
cnt2IfNumEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

cnt2IfNumIndex.name: cnt2IfNumIndex
cnt2IfNumIndex.description: The slot number 1-12 for this table entry.

cnt2IfNum.name: cnt2IfNum
cnt2IfNum.description: The number of network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this slot.

cnt2IfTable.name: cnt2IfTable
cnt2IfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of cnt2IfNumber.

cnt2IfEntry.name: cnt2IfEntry
cnt2IfEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

cnt2IfSlotIndex.name: cnt2IfSlotIndex
cnt2IfSlotIndex.description: The slot number 1-12 for this table entry.

cnt2IfIndex.name: cnt2IfIndex
cnt2IfIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of cnt2IfNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

cnt2IfDescr.name: cnt2IfDescr
cnt2IfDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.

cnt2IfType.name: cnt2IfType
cnt2IfType.description: The type of interface, distinguished according to the physical/link protocol(s) immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack.

cnt2IfMtu.name: cnt2IfMtu
cnt2IfMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

cnt2IfSpeed.name: cnt2IfSpeed
cnt2IfSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth.

cnt2IfPhysAddress.name: cnt2IfPhysAddress
cnt2IfPhysAddress.description: The interface's address at the protocol layer immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

cnt2IfAdminStatus.name: cnt2IfAdminStatus
cnt2IfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

cnt2IfOperStatus.name: cnt2IfOperStatus
cnt2IfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

cnt2IfLastChange.name: cnt2IfLastChange
cnt2IfLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

cnt2IfInOctets.name: cnt2IfInOctets
cnt2IfInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

cnt2IfInUcastPkts.name: cnt2IfInUcastPkts
cnt2IfInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

cnt2IfInNUcastPkts.name: cnt2IfInNUcastPkts
cnt2IfInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

cnt2IfInDiscards.name: cnt2IfInDiscards
cnt2IfInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

cnt2IfInErrors.name: cnt2IfInErrors
cnt2IfInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

cnt2IfInUnknownProtos.name: cnt2IfInUnknownProtos
cnt2IfInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

cnt2IfOutOctets.name: cnt2IfOutOctets
cnt2IfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

cnt2IfOutUcastPkts.name: cnt2IfOutUcastPkts
cnt2IfOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cnt2IfOutNUcastPkts.name: cnt2IfOutNUcastPkts
cnt2IfOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cnt2IfOutDiscards.name: cnt2IfOutDiscards
cnt2IfOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

cnt2IfOutErrors.name: cnt2IfOutErrors
cnt2IfOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

cnt2IfOutQLen.name: cnt2IfOutQLen
cnt2IfOutQLen.description: The length of the output packet queue (in packets).

cnt2IfSpecific.name: cnt2IfSpecific
cnt2IfSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular media being used to realize the interface. For example, if the interface is realized by an ethernet, then the value of this object refers to a document defining objects specific to ethernet. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntatically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.

cnt2XIfTable.name: cnt2XIfTable
cnt2XIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of cnt2XIfNumber.

cnt2XIfEntry.name: cnt2XIfEntry
cnt2XIfEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

cnt2XIfSlotIndex.name: cnt2XIfSlotIndex
cnt2XIfSlotIndex.description: The slot number 1-4 for this table entry.

cnt2XIfIndex.name: cnt2XIfIndex
cnt2XIfIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of cnt2IfNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

cnt2XIfDescr.name: cnt2XIfDescr
cnt2XIfDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.

cnt2XIfName.name: cnt2XIfName
cnt2XIfName.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.

cnt2XIfIANAType.name: cnt2XIfIANAType
cnt2XIfIANAType.description: The type of interface. Additional values for ifType are assigned by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (IANA), through updating the syntax of the IANAifType textual convention.

cnt2XIfCntType.name: cnt2XIfCntType
cnt2XIfCntType.description: The type of interface, distinguished according to the physical/link protocol(s) immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack.

cnt2XIfMtu.name: cnt2XIfMtu
cnt2XIfMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

cnt2XIfSpeed.name: cnt2XIfSpeed
cnt2XIfSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth.

cnt2XIfPhysAddress.name: cnt2XIfPhysAddress
cnt2XIfPhysAddress.description: The interface's address at the protocol layer immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

cnt2XIfAdminStatus.name: cnt2XIfAdminStatus
cnt2XIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

cnt2XIfOperStatus.name: cnt2XIfOperStatus
cnt2XIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

cnt2XIfLastChange.name: cnt2XIfLastChange
cnt2XIfLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

cnt2XIfLinkUpDownTrapEnable.name: cnt2XIfLinkUpDownTrapEnable
cnt2XIfLinkUpDownTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether linkUp/linkDown traps should be generated for this interface. By default, this object should have the value enabled(1) for interfaces which do not operate on 'top' of any other interface (as defined in the ifStackTable), and disabled(2) otherwise.

cnt2XIfPromiscuousMode.name: cnt2XIfPromiscuousMode
cnt2XIfPromiscuousMode.description: This object has a value of false(2) if this interface only accepts packets/frames that are addressed to this station. This object has a value of true(1) when the station accepts all packets/frames transmitted on the media. The value true(1) is only legal on certain types of media. If legal, setting this object to a value of true(1) may require the interface to be reset before becoming effective. The value of ifPromiscuousMode does not affect the reception of broadcast and multicast packets/frames by the interface.

cnt2XIfConnectorType.name: cnt2XIfConnectorType
cnt2XIfConnectorType.description: This object has the value 'true(1)' if the interface sublayer has a physical connector and the value 'false(2)' otherwise.

cnt2XIfAlias.name: cnt2XIfAlias
cnt2XIfAlias.description: This object is an 'alias' name for the interface as specified by a network manager, and provides a non- volatile 'handle' for the interface. On the first instantiation of an interface, the value of ifAlias associated with that interface is the zero-length string. As and when a value is written into an instance of ifAlias through a network management set operation, then the agent must retain the supplied value in the ifAlias instance associated with the same interface for as long as that interface remains instantiated, including across all re- initializations/reboots of the network management system, including those which result in a change of the interface's ifIndex value. An example of the value which a network manager might store in this object for a WAN interface is the (Telco's) circuit number/identifier of the interface. Some agents may support write-access only for interfaces having particular values of ifType. An agent which supports write access to this object is required to keep the value in non-volatile storage, but it may limit the length of new values depending on how much storage is already occupied by the current values for other interfaces.

cnt2XIfInOctets.name: cnt2XIfInOctets
cnt2XIfInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

cnt2XIfInUcastPkts.name: cnt2XIfInUcastPkts
cnt2XIfInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

cnt2XIfInMulticastPkts.name: cnt2XIfInMulticastPkts
cnt2XIfInMulticastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cnt2XIfInBroadcastPkts.name: cnt2XIfInBroadcastPkts
cnt2XIfInBroadcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cnt2XIfInDiscards.name: cnt2XIfInDiscards
cnt2XIfInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

cnt2XIfInErrors.name: cnt2XIfInErrors
cnt2XIfInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

cnt2XIfInUnknownProtos.name: cnt2XIfInUnknownProtos
cnt2XIfInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

cnt2XIfOutOctets.name: cnt2XIfOutOctets
cnt2XIfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

cnt2XIfOutUcastPkts.name: cnt2XIfOutUcastPkts
cnt2XIfOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cnt2XIfOutMulticastPkts.name: cnt2XIfOutMulticastPkts
cnt2XIfOutMulticastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cnt2XIfOutBroadcastPkts.name: cnt2XIfOutBroadcastPkts
cnt2XIfOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cnt2XIfOutDiscards.name: cnt2XIfOutDiscards
cnt2XIfOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

cnt2XIfOutErrors.name: cnt2XIfOutErrors
cnt2XIfOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

cnt2XIfCounterDiscontinuityTime.name: cnt2XIfCounterDiscontinuityTime
cnt2XIfCounterDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one or more of this interface's counters suffered a discontinuity. The relevant counters are the specific instances associated with this interface of any Counter32 or Counter64 object contained in the ifTable or ifXTable. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re-initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.
